translated: Örnefors, Fritz Einar Vitalis, district physician, Hohultslätt, no. Årjäng, b. 16/3/05 in Viitsand, Värmland. Firstborn. Completed studies in Karlstad in 1926, obtained Bachelor's degree in Medicine in Uppsala in 1929, and obtained Medical license in Stockholm in 1935. Assistant physician at Sachsska Children's Hospital in 1935, resident physician at Marieberg Hospital in 1936, assistant physician and temporary deputy senior physician at Karlstad County Hospital Medical Department from 1936-1937, temporary deputy physician at Mohed Sanatorium in 1938, appointed deputy physician in the same year. Became deputy physician at S:t Gertrud Hospital, Sundsvalls Hospital, Växjö Hospital, and Eskilstuna Hospital from 1940-1946. Became district physician in Hohultslätt district in 1946-1947, and provincial physician in Årjäng from 1947 onwards.
